<topic class="Popup" template="Default" status="Under Construction" modified="2023-10-13T16:24:02.944+01:00" lasteditedby="44785" version="2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../../helpproject.xsd">
  <title>Follower-Profile-Shapes</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Follower-Profile Shapes<keyword>Flat-faced Follower</keyword><keyword>Follower-Roller (circular)</keyword><keyword>Knife-Edged Follower</keyword><keyword>Lozenge Follower-Profile</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="6" colcount="2" style="width:450px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Follower-Profile Shapes</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Follower-Profile:</text> the shape that is in continuous contact with the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Cam</text>. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Follower-Profile: </text>a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">sketch-loop</text> with a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Profile</text> / <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Extrusion</text>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="VariableName-small">Follower Shapes</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:89px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-CircularCamFollower-Ex-Pop.ipp" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="VariableName-small">1: Follower-Roller</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Circle</text> represents a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Follower-Roller.</text>&#32;</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="Popup Box">It represents a bearing or Pin that is a </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Cylindrical</text><text styleclass="Popup Box">, or </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Crown/Barrel shaped. </text><text styleclass="Popup Box">It is the most common shape for a </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Follower-Profile</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:89px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-FlatFacedFollower-Ex-pop.ipp" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="VariableName-small">2: Flat-faced Follower </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The 4×<text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Lines</text> as a sketch of a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">long</text> rectangle represents a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Flat-Faced-Follower</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The <text styleclass="VariableName-small">rectangle</text> must be long enough so that the Flat-Face is always in contact with the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Cam-Profile</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:89px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-ContourCamFollower-Ex-Pop.ipp" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="VariableName-small">3: Multi-Contour Follower </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">For example, four Arcs, with Tangent constraints,</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">joined as an ellipse.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:89px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-KnifeEdged-CamFollower-Ex-pop.ipp" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="VariableName-small">4: Knife-Edged Follower</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">An <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">arc</text>, with a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">small</text> radius. The small <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Arc</text> represent the knife-edge. A true knife-edge is not practically possible. </para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
